page.title: 07FLOWERS ON BISHOPSTONE DOWN.
page.content: ALONG THE REMAINING HEDGEROWS, ALONGSIDE THE FOOTPATHS AND TRACKS IN FIELDS AND IN AREAS TOO STEEP FOR THE PLOUGH A VARIETY OF WILD FLOWERS GROW. THESE HAVE ALL BEEN SEEN ON THE HILLS THIS SUMMER-BINDWEED- BLACK SMALL AND LARGER;BURNET SAXIFRAGE; CAMPION-WHITE; CHALK MILKWORT; CHICKWEED, CLOVER-RED AND WHITE; CORN CHAMOMILE, DAISY, DOCKS, FORGET- ME- NOT, GROUNDSEL, HAREBELL, HAWKBIT-ROUGH;HEATSEASE-WILD PANSY; KNAPWEED,MEADOW CRANESBILL, NETTLES- WHITE DEAD AND STINGING,PLAINTAIN- HAIRY AND GREATER,POPPY-FIELD, RAGWORT,COMMON;RAYLESS MAYWEED, SCABIOUS;SHEPHERDS PURBER;SILVERWEED; SOWTHISTLE-CORN AND COMMON;THISTLES; TOADFLAX-COMMON;YARROW;
